1 Sec. 2. RESIDENTIAL PEER RESPITE FACILITY
2 (a) The Department of Mental Health shall issue a request for proposals to
3 establish a two-bed residential peer respite facility in southern Vermont based
4 on an existing model that provides supports and services to individuals
5 experiencing a mental health crisis.
6 (b) A successful applicant shall ensure that:
7 (1) at least one bed in the facility may be reserved for stays of up to four
8 weeks; and
9 (2) the remaining bed is reserved for short-term residential stays of up to
10 two weeks.
11 (c) On or before January 1, 2026, the Department shall contract with an
12 eligible applicant to establish and operate a residential peer respite facility in
13 accordance with this section.
14 Sec. 3. APPROPRIATION; RESIDENTIAL PEER RESPITE FACILITY
15 In fiscal year 2026, $515,000.00 is appropriated from the General Fund to
16 the Department of Mental Health for the purpose of contracting with an entity
17 to establish and operate a residential peer respite facility pursuant to Sec. 2
18 (residential peer respite facility) of this act.
19 Sec. 4. EFFECTIVE DATE
20 This act shall take effect on July 1, 2025.
